.Dd April 5, 2026
.Dt GHOSTLINE_CLI 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm ghostline_cli
.Nd transport-first interception relay with candidate mutation, rules loading, target discovery, and operator review workflows
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar listen_port upstream_host upstream_port
.Op options
.Nm
.Fl -search-pid Ar term
.Op search options
.Nm
.Fl -review-list
.Op review options
.Nm
.Fl -help-rules | -help-search | -help-profiles | -help-review | -help-examples | -help-cheatsheet
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is the Ghostline Phase 1 command-line operator surface.
It relays TCP traffic, stages mutation candidates, validates modified output before release, and falls back to original delivery when mutation safety is not provable.
.Pp
Ghostline is built around one operating rule:
.Dq original delivery wins unless modified release is proven safe .
.Pp
The CLI supports:
.Bl -bullet
.It
raw live mutation
.It
byte-window mutation
.It
MQTT framing and
.Dq PUBLISH
mutation
.It
rules-driven configuration via JSON, Jinja-style JSON, and lightweight HCL/Terraform-style files
.It
PID and port discovery for target selection
.It
saved target profiles
.It
pending review queue operations
.It
human-readable and JSONL audit and action streams
.El
.Sh OPERATING MODEL
Ghostline is transport-first rather than protocol-first.
It keeps original delivery available while plugins attempt framing or mutation.
Modified bytes are released only after validation succeeds.
When mutation fails or becomes structurally unsafe, Ghostline releases the untouched original bytes and may create an operator review item instead of forcing the modified path.
.Pp
Current protocol reality:
.Bl -bullet
.It
MQTT is the only protocol-owned framing and active mutation plugin.
.It
raw-live and byte-window cover unknown traffic and operator-defined boundaries.
.It
RabbitMQ, AMQP, ActiveMQ, Azure Service Bus, and Kafka are compiled-in detection and audit targets today.
.El
.Sh CORE OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--mqtt-review-threshold"
.It Fl -start-hex Ar hex
Start marker for the byte-window plugin.
.It Fl -end-hex Ar hex
End marker for the byte-window plugin.
.It Fl -replace-text Ar text
Replacement body for matched windows or payloads.
.It Fl -raw-find-text Ar text
Find text for raw live mutation.
.It Fl -raw-live
Enable protocol-agnostic live raw mutation.
.It Fl -raw-chunk-bytes Ar n
Frame raw live traffic into fixed-size chunks.
.It Fl -mutate-direction Ar c2s|s2c|both
Choose which direction may mutate.
.It Fl -raw-review-threshold Ar n
Create review/action items for raw mutations at or above this byte size.
.It Fl -mqtt-review-threshold Ar n
Create review/action items for MQTT mutations at or above this payload size.
.It Fl -byte-review-threshold Ar n
Create review/action items for byte-window mutations at or above this payload size.
.It Fl -rewrite-u32-prefix
Rewrite a leading 4-byte big-endian body size when applicable.
.It Fl -max-plugin-buffer Ar n
Maximum bytes a protocol plugin may hold before fallback-to-original behavior is triggered.
.It Fl -protocol-hint Ar name
Prefer a compiled-in plugin:
.Dq mqtt ,
.Dq rabbitmq ,
.Dq activemq ,
.Dq amqp ,
.Dq azure-service-bus ,
.Dq kafka ,
.Dq byte-window ,
or
.Dq raw-live .
.El
.Sh RULES OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--rules-var"
.It Fl -rules Ar path
Load external control rules from JSON, Jinja-style JSON, or a lightweight HCL/Terraform-style flat config.
.It Fl -rules-var Ar key=value
Template variable used when rendering Jinja-style rules.
.El
.Pp
Common rule keys include:
.Bl -bullet
.It
listen_port, upstream_host, upstream_port
.It
protocol_hint, start_marker_hex, end_marker_hex
.It
replace_text, raw_find_text, raw_live, raw_live_mode
.It
raw_chunk_bytes, mutate_direction, rewrite_u32_prefix
.It
raw_review_threshold_bytes, mqtt_review_threshold_bytes
.It
byte_window_review_threshold_bytes, max_plugin_buffer_bytes
.It
audit_log_path, action_log_path, audit_json_path, action_json_path
.It
review_queue_dir
.El
.Sh SEARCH OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--established-only"
.It Fl -search-pid Ar term
Search running TCP processes by command substring or PID.
.It Fl -search-port Ar port
Filter search results by local or remote TCP port.
.It Fl -search-state Ar state
Filter results by TCP state such as
.Dq LISTEN
or
.Dq ESTABLISHED .
.It Fl -search-json
Emit search results as JSON.
.It Fl -listen-only
Restrict results to listening sockets.
.It Fl -established-only
Restrict results to established sockets.
.El
.Pp
PID discovery is a targeting feature.
It does not turn PID identity into the transport routing primitive.
.Sh PROFILE OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--seed-target-profiles"
.It Fl -save-target-profile Ar path
Write a target profile to disk.
.It Fl -target-label Ar label
Label used when saving a target profile.
.It Fl -load-target-profile Ar path
Load a saved target profile into search mode.
.It Fl -show-target-profile Ar path
Print a saved target profile.
.It Fl -list-target-profiles Ar dir
List saved target profile files.
.It Fl -seed-target-profiles Ar dir
Write ready-to-use protocol target profiles for MQTT, RMQ, AMQP, ActiveMQ, Azure Service Bus, and Kafka.
.El
.Sh REVIEW OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--review-replay"
.It Fl -review-list
List pending and saved review items.
.It Fl -review-approve Ar action_id
Mark a review item approved.
.It Fl -review-reject Ar action_id
Mark a review item rejected.
.It Fl -review-replay Ar action_id
Create a replay artifact from a blocked or saved mutation review.
.It Fl -review-note Ar text
Decision note for approve, reject, or replay operations.
.It Fl -review-queue-dir Ar dir
Directory containing saved review items.
.It Fl -replay-dir Ar dir
Directory where replay artifacts are written.
.El
.Pp
Replay currently creates an operator artifact for follow-up.
It does not inject traffic back into a live flow.
.Sh OUTPUT OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--actions-json"
.It Fl -audit-log Ar path
Write text audit events to the given file.
.It Fl -audit-json Ar path
Write audit events as JSONL.
.It Fl -action-log Ar path
Write text action items to the given file.
.It Fl -actions-json Ar path
Write action items as JSONL.
.El
.Pp
JSONL outputs are the recommended bridge for Python or Lua adapters because they avoid scraping human-readable logs.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -bullet
.It
Search for a process:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli --search-pid ollama
.Ed
.It
Search for listeners on MQTT port 1883:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli --search-port 1883 --listen-only
.Ed
.It
Seed protocol target profiles:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli --seed-target-profiles ghostline_target_profiles
.Ed
.It
Run raw live mutation:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli 7777 127.0.0.1 8888 \e
  --protocol-hint raw-live \e
  --raw-live \e
  --raw-find-text hello \e
  --replace-text patch \e
  --mutate-direction c2s \e
  --raw-review-threshold 8
.Ed
.It
Run MQTT mutation:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli 7777 127.0.0.1 1883 \e
  --protocol-hint mqtt \e
  --replace-text patched-payload \e
  --mutate-direction c2s \e
  --mqtt-review-threshold 8
.Ed
.It
Run from JSON rules:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli 7777 127.0.0.1 8888 \e
  --rules examples/rules/raw-live.json
.Ed
.It
Emit JSONL audit and action streams:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli 7777 127.0.0.1 8888 \e
  --rules examples/rules/raw-live.json \e
  --audit-json ghostline_audit.jsonl \e
  --actions-json ghostline_actions.jsonl
.Ed
.It
Work the review queue:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ghostline_cli --review-list
ghostline_cli --review-approve action-1-3 --review-note approved
ghostline_cli --review-replay action-1-3 --review-note replay-now
.Ed
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -bullet
.It
.Pa ghostline_audit.log
default text audit output
.It
.Pa ghostline_actions.log
default text action output
.It
.Pa ghostline_review_queue/
saved review items
.It
.Pa ghostline_replays/
replay artifacts
.It
.Pa ghostline_target_profiles/
saved and seeded target profiles
.El
.Sh QT OPERATOR APP
When Qt6 Widgets is available and the Qt target is built, the companion app is:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
./build-local/ghostline_qt
.Ed
.Pp
The Qt operator app currently supports target discovery, target profiles, review queue operations, and loading rules and JSONL files from disk.
.Sh MAN PAGE
To open this man page from the repository root:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
MANPATH="$PWD/man:${MANPATH}" man ghostline_cli
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr man 1
